<plot>Reshaping our bodies using plastic surgery seems a wonder of modern medicine. But new evidence suggests that people have been surgically altering themselves for thousands of years. This two-hour special discovers nose restorations, breast reductions, eyelid tucks, face lifts, counter-circumcision and even a sex-change were all being carried out two thousand years ago.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?038935</url></doc>
